From 97e16dfd1f17729c59a2e8df259a8798a53d4b45 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Narendhar Reddy <nare@qti.qualcomm.com>
Date: Wed, 24 Sep 2025 10:25:33 +0530
Subject: [PATCH] QSDK:PLATFORM:ath12k: set mhi state to off instead of
 suspend.

Currently after coldboot calibration, ath12k is sending
POWER_OFF_KEP_DEV instead of POWER_OFF, which is setting MHI to
wrong state before deinit, which leads to failure in subsequent
power up.

Fix this by setting the state to POWER_OFF

Signed-off-by: Narendhar Reddy <nare@qti.qualcomm.com>
---
 drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/qmi.c | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/qmi.c b/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/qmi.c
index df29c32..45c7b30 100644
--- a/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/qmi.c
+++ b/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/qmi.c
@@ -5314,7 +5314,7 @@ int ath12k_qmi_process_coldboot_calibration(struct ath12k_base *ab)
 	ath12k_qmi_firmware_stop(ab);
 
 	if (!ab->pm_suspend)
-		ath12k_hif_power_down(ab, true);
+		ath12k_hif_power_down(ab, false);
 
 	ath12k_qmi_free_target_mem_chunk(ab);
 	ath12k_info(ab, "power up to restart firmware in mission mode\n");
-- 
2.34.1

